== Description == <!--T:3-->

<!--T:4-->
The [[Image:Assembly_New_Group.svg‎‎|24px]] [[Assembly3_GroupObjects|Group objects]] command adds a new (sub-) '''Group''' folder object to the Assembly branch of the model tree.

<!--T:5-->
It can be used to either group '''Constraints''', '''Elements''', or '''Parts''' and will be inserted into the selected objects' group containers ([[Image:Assembly_Assembly_Constraints_Tree.svg|24px]] '''Constraints''',  [[Image:Assembly_Assembly_Element_Tree.svg|24px]] '''Elements''', or  [[Image:Assembly_Assembly_Part_Tree.svg|24px]] '''Parts''')

== Usage == <!--T:6-->

<!--T:7-->
# Select several '''constraints''', several '''elements''', or several '''parts''' from the assembly tree
# There are several ways to invoke the command:
#* Press the {{Button|[[Image:Assembly_New_Group.svg‎‎|16px]] [[Assembly3_GroupObjects|Group objects]]}} button.
#* Select the {{MenuCommand|Assembly3 → [[Image:Assembly_New_Group.svg‎‎|16px]] Group objects}} option from the menu.
#* Use the keyboard shortcut {{KEY|A}} then {{KEY|Z}}

<!--T:8-->
: If the selection contains different types of objects the {{Button|[[Image:Assembly_New_Group.svg‎‎|16px]] [[Assembly3_GroupObjects|Group objects]]}} button will be inactive.


